comments:
I noticed patterns at the beginning of the syllabi of the word as the shape or format of the object, and the last syllabi as the color of the object.

At the start, it was difficult to memorize, but I made an effort to understand the shape, and there onwards, after having a solid grasp of the shape, I made an effort to understand the color.

I used no paper and no other techniques than my mind itself. I thought the tasks at the end were much easier than the ones at the start, and perhaps I would've learned better by starting at the last tasks and coming back to the first ones.

Naming the objects was especially hard at the start, while identifying them in the second part was much easier.
